Description: Papyrus written with black ink with demotic legal text on recto (6 ll.), verso blank. Thompson's MS Catalogue: "Receipt for corn by Twot son of Petetumis to his half-brother Tef-Hap. Date none. [Ptolemy Philometor]". Nos. 10575-10601 from the Siut Archive.
Curator's comments: Published: A. F. Shore and H. S. Smith 'Two Unpublished Demotic Documents from the Asyut Archive'. JEA 465 (1959), 52-60.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (45566) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/45566)
Condition: Papyrus Survey: Condition Details: Papyrus: fractured, dirty Black ink Tabbed: kraft paper Mount Details: Sandwich: glass Binding: cloth Object Priority: B Mount Priority: A Overall Condition: B Curatorial condition comment: good
Acquisition notes: Purchased from M. Nahman. Cf. the additional sheets at the end of Thompson's MS Catalogue, titled "B.M. Nahman Papyri (1923)".
